# Game UI

## DOM overlays on canvas

- UI is HTML/CSS over the canvas — keep game logic out of UI event handlers; call game callbacks.
- New screens: prefer a dedicated section or small module, not 200 more lines in `UI.js`.

## Accessibility & input

- Keyboard: document new bindings in README controls table.
- Don't steal focus from canvas movement keys when menus are closed.

## Styling

- Use existing CSS variables and panel patterns in `style.css`.
- Mobile: test touch targets if adding interactive HUD elements.

## Feedback

- Combat feedback (damage numbers, crits) — keep allocation pooled; no DOM node per hit in horde scenarios.
- Level-up and shop UIs must handle edge cases (empty choices, max level) with user-visible errors, not silent `console.error` only.
